FT  10 AUG 93 / Management (The Growing Business): Making a break to East
Asia - In a nutshell
A business centre to help local companies break into export markets in the
Far East and Asia has been launched by Rochdale Training and Enterprise
Council.
The Trading and Training Services Centre offers help with marketing and
sales in areas such as China, Japan, Taiwan and Korea. It provides
assistance with translations, market research, joint ventures and
information on legislation, duties and tariffs.
The centre recently helped local businesses establish links with a visiting
trade delegation from Malaysia.
Contact Philomena Lee-Yeun Chen. Rochdale TEC, St James Place, 160-162
Yorkshire Street, Rochdale, Lancashire, OL16 2DL. Tel 0706 44909.
